<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2438: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-26T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            26, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>6005. Your 3113, September 25, 6 p.m.</p>
                            <p>While not desiring to interfere with your discretion in this matter
                                the Department hopes that you may find it possible to impress upon
                                the British Government the urgency of the situation and the danger
                                that the delay in the Japanese reply may so far protract the
                                negotiations as to defeat their purpose.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>